    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-21T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/11–2944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>, Political Adviser,
                        Allied Force Headquarters at Caserta</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-21T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 21, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Barnes, Sofia, 14.</p>
                <p>For Berry, Bucharest, 32.</p>
                <p>Reurtel 1533, November 29.<note n="90" xml:id="d446fn90">Not printed.</note>
                    Department now giving consideration to British proposal for establishment of
                    restitution commission details of which have just been received.</p>
                <p>However, it is not desired that negotiations for establishment of restitution
                    commission should delay recovery of identifiable looted Greek property by Greece
                    from Bulgaria.</p>
                <p>ACC should nevertheless make it clear to Greek authorities that it can accept no
                    liability for deciding true ownership in handing over property for which prima
                    facie claims have been made.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Athens 139, Moscow 2867, and London 10634.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
